ed at by privileging a handful of texts.This study of Cyprian's appropriation of Pauline texts therefore illuminates the interplay between text, context and theology in his exegesis. It also deepens our understanding of the early North African hermeneutical tradition and the early reception of Paul.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Okt 2018) 4aEarly Christian Theology. 4aHermeneutics. 4aLatin Christianity, Patristic exegesis, Hermeneutics, Early Christian Theology. 4aLatin Christianity. 4aPatristic Exegesis.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishz978311060425208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018z9783110603255oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2018 Englishz978311060424508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theology, Relig. Studies, Jewish Studies 2018z9783110603248oZDB-23-DGF0 cEPUBz97831106001620 cprintz978311060103940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110600186423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110600186.jpg  a978-3-11-060424-5  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig. Stud., Jewish Stud.2018 Englishb2018  a978-3-11-060425-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2018 Englishb2018  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG  aZDB-23-DGFb2018  aZDB-23-DGGb2017